Package: cptkirk
Title: Warp-Speed Remote GDAL Warping of Cloud-Optimised GeoTIFFs
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Hugh", "Graham", , "hugh@belian.earth", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Warps remote Cloud-Optimised GeoTIFFs at speed by saturating the
    network with concurrent byte-range reads. cptkirk works out which source
    pixels a requested warp will touch, streams only those tiles over the Rust
    'async-tiff' reader (at the appropriate overview level), stages them as an
    in-memory GDAL source, then hands the actual reprojection and resampling to
    GDAL via 'gdalraster', following the gdalwarp argument interface.
